This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on the generalization ability of neural networks on learning simple algorithms. It also involves the analysis of memory-augmented neural networks, which is a popular topic in the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the working mechanism of memory modules in neural networks. The paper also involves the analysis of the strategies learned by the models, which may fall under the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields often involve the analysis of patterns and strategies in data.
